# Story Canon

Canonical: `Documents/03_World/StoryBible.md`, `FacilityBible.md`, `RoomBible.md`, plus `Documents/01_Game_Design/NarrativeDesign.md`.

## Delivery

- Environmental storytelling over exposition dumps.
- Notes and props = residue of work and failure — not quest markers in prose.
- **Symptoms, not walkthroughs.** Forbidden: “go north then pick up the fuse/fuel.”
- No audio-log monologues unless the approved brief requires them.

## Facility realism

- Rooms have function, what happened, and why the player is there (Room Bible).
- Asterion is a real workplace that failed — tone stays isolated, scientific, grounded.
- Power literacy is layered (aux vs main) when teaching Engineering beats.

## Witness

- Uncertainty and presence; do not over-explain The Witness in player-facing text.
- Narrative pressure must not brick solvable gameplay.

## Conflicts

If a mission note or beat conflicts with Story / Facility / Room bibles, stop and resolve via ADR or EP clarification before shipping.
